00:38:37.350 --> 00:38:38.650
&gt;&gt; Ira Glasser: One of the
things that's really interesting

00:38:38.650 --> 00:38:43.370
about all demonstrations, and so
many of Bob's pictures show this,

00:38:43.370 --> 00:38:49.420
is that the violent reaction that
peaceful demonstrators provoke

00:38:49.420 --> 00:38:54.090
in people who are opposed to
the content of what they say.

00:38:54.090 --> 00:38:57.910
You know, sometimes the violence
is by construction workers.

00:38:57.910 --> 00:39:00.460
Sometimes the violence
was by men against women.

00:39:00.460 --> 00:39:02.220
Sometimes it was by
whites against blacks.

00:39:02.220 --> 00:39:04.370
Sometimes it was by
straights against gays.

00:39:04.370 --> 00:39:05.670
But it's always the same.

00:39:05.670 --> 00:39:11.650
There's always this almost
deformed look of anger and hatred,

00:39:11.650 --> 00:39:15.890
and impending imminent violence
that people who are opposed

00:39:15.890 --> 00:39:20.940
to the content of what is
being said feel on the outside.

00:39:20.940 --> 00:39:22.690
And all of those --
that's why it's very hard,

00:39:22.690 --> 00:39:25.840
unless you've taken the pictures,
to know where they're from,

00:39:25.840 --> 00:39:30.000
because there's something very
similar about all those faces.

00:39:43.710 --> 00:39:47.570
Susan B. Anthony, by the way, was a
very big supporter of prohibition,

00:39:47.570 --> 00:39:52.230
just to balance things out a little
bit, and all of the depredations

00:39:52.230 --> 00:39:58.000
of liberty that that involves and
